<section id="features">
    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li> General astronomical image and data analysis</li>
        <li> Interactive image display similar to DS9</li>
        <li> Reads and writes standard FITS images and tables, including FPACK compressed, and 3D image cubes</li>
        <li> TESS image (e.g. TESScut) and SPOC lightcurve analysis</li>
        <li> FITS header viewing and editing</li>
        <li> Plate solving via Astrometry.net web interface (local solver capability on Microsoft Windows)</li>
        <li> Displays astronomical coordinates at mouse pointer for images with WCS headers</li>
        <li> Provides object identification via an embedded SIMBAD interface</li>
        <li> Aligns image sequences using WCS headers or by using apertures to correlate stars</li>
        <li> Image calibration including bias, dark, flat, and non-linearity correction with option to run in real-time</li>
        <li> Interactive time-series differential photometry interface with option to run in real-time</li>
        <li> Various aperture options (fixed, auto-fixed, variable size; circular, elliptical, arbitrary shape)</li>
        <li> Comparison ensemble apertures can optionally be automatically selected in images</li>
        <li> Time-series photometry of moving objects (such as asteroids, etc.)</li>
        <li> Comparison star ensemble and detrend can be changed without re-running differential photometry</li>
        <li> Interactive multi-curve plotting tool streamlined for plotting light curves</li>
        <li> Automated plot titling capability (from FITS headers, measurements tables, filenames)</li>
        <li> Interactive light curve fitting interface with simultaneous detrending</li>
        <li> Automated comparison ensemble and detrend optimization and light curve outlier removal</li>
        <li> Non-destructive object annotations/labels using FITS header keywords</li>
        <li> Time and coordinate conversion with capability to update/enhance FITS header content (AIRMASS, BJD, etc.)</li>
        <li> Powerful photometry table (measurements table) editing</li>
        <li> Handling of debayering of color images</li>
        <li> Optionally enter reference star apparent magnitudes to calculate target star magnitudes automatically </li>
        <li> Optionally create Minor Planet Center (MPC) format for direct submission of data to the MPC</li>
        <li> Optionally create AAVSO formatted lightcurves</li>
        <li> Automated check for nearby eclipsing binary signals for TESS follow-up (thanks to Dennis Conti)</li>
    </ul>
